      "writtenOn": "2016-12-02T16:57:25Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Actually, similarly to the 3-component matrix-based (ie XZYTRC) profiles where it says the A2B tags may be included, it says the same thing for monochrome (ie gray, kTRC) profiles. So maybe we should ignore it.\n\nWith the A2B before XYZ refactor it would be getting hit anyway. I\u0027ll just remove this. If the A2B tags aren\u0027t nicely defined the monochrome they won\u0027t successfully parse anyway. This would mean that I can\u0027t use InputColorFormat \u003d\u003d kGray to insert the whitepoint adjustment though, but I could just put an additional check for there being only 1 input channel, if the A2B tags happen to use the CLUT to do whitepoint adjustment.",
