      "side": 1,
      "message": "Right, I forgot about that PCSLAB \u003d\u003e n-component LUT-based profile, and that gray profiles are a 3rd separate kind of profile.\n\nI wonder, should they even be in the A2B ColorSpace then? At least if the swizzler still copies the gray channel to all 3 colour channels (is it the same to all 3?), then you could probably just specify the whitepoint adjustment as a matrix, then duplicate the  gray TRC into 3 channels. You\u0027d be taking the XYZ xform instead of the A2B xform, but would also be evaluating the TRC 3 times as much, and removing the possibility of only passing in the red(gray) buffer and having a special load_gray stage that does 8bit grayscale buffers and stores them in r.",
